		</Row>

		<!-- Leader specific pedia text. -->
		<Row Tag="LOC_PEDIA_LEADERS_PAGE_LEADER_NEPHI_CHAPTER_CAPSULE_BODY" Language="en_US">
			<Text>Nephi, the fourth son of Lehi, is obedient to all the commandments of the Lord.</Text>
		</Row>
		<Row Tag="LOC_PEDIA_LEADERS_PAGE_LEADER_NEPHI_CHAPTER_DETAILED_BODY" Language="en_US">
			<Text>Nephi's strict obedience inspires his people to be industrious and righteous.</Text>
		</Row>
		
		<!-- Leader specific historical text. -->
		<Row Tag="LOC_PEDIA_LEADERS_PAGE_LEADER_NEPHI_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1" Language="en_US">
			<Text>Born in Jerusalem, Nephi's father, Lehi, took his entire family and some other followers into the wilderness
			in 600 BC, shortly before Jerusalem was conquered by the Babylonians. After many years in the wilderness, a gruelling
			voyage across the sea, and constant fighting with his older brothers, Laman and Lemuel, Nephi became a leader among
			this brand new civilization.</Text>
		</Row>

		<!-- Civilization specific historical text. -->
		<Row Tag="LOC_PEDIA_CIVILIZATIONS_PAGE_CIVILIZATION_NEPHITES_CHAPTER_HISTORY_PARA_1" Language="en_US">
			<Text>The Nephite civilization began with Nephi, after he and his followers fled from his brothers, Laman and Lemuel,
			around 600 BC. The Nephite rulers kept a careful record of all their dealings, which was summarized by Mormon around 
			400 AD.</Text>
		</Row>

